{
  "stem": "6845.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was no joke, because it was no-- there was no end to it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was just tremendously deep and steep.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I remember for the rest of my life, when I say, outhouse, I just think of Martha, and me, and our paintings.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But we did lots of fun things, and school was not really the right school for us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, for me, it was difficult because they expected to-- that I speak now Czech, instead of Slovak.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was very, very difficult.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So anyway, after the year was over, I convinced my parents I want to go back to another school, a high school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's what I did, because Martha would go, and all my friends, and not the gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The gymnasium requested to study, right away, Latin-- and very seriously-- and one other foreign language.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't German.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It wasn't French.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think Russian, Russian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I said to my parents, I don't want it now.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Why don't I just go to high school?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then I ended up with business school, a business academy for two years, and I graduated there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I still learned lots of things there in the schools, which I don't think people are as well-prepared here, because from bookkeeping, to languages, to different s-- speed writing, to take shorthand writing-- I tell you, I was so well-prepared, I-- really.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the school was no problem.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I always-- once I liked it, I-- I did real well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the first year was very difficult, because, as I said, with the Latin and the Russian, it was just too much-- two extra new languages.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my parents moved in, themselves, to the city, by the time I was 13-- 12 or 13.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
